<zk>
	<label multiline="true">
How to reproduce ZK-5686 (before the fix)

Setup:
	An outer ZUL applies an inner ZUL via &lt;apply templateURI="..."/&gt;.
	The inner ZUL declares a namespace on its root (xmlns:w="client") and
	uses that prefix on a child attribute (w:onClick="...").

Trigger path (zklinter):
	zklinter's ZulParser resolves the &lt;apply&gt; by calling
	cloneNode(true) on the included root, then appendChild to the outer
	tree (zkcml/zklinter/.../ZulParser.java around line 190).
	cloneNode -&gt; Element.clone() detaches the cloned subtree from its
	parent (AbstractItem.clone sets _parent = null) and copies only the
	element's own _addNamespaces. The cloned attributes still carry the
	w prefix, but the cloned owner can no longer resolve it through the
	parent chain.

Failure:
	Re-attaching cloned attributes via AttrArray.checkAdd ->
	Attribute.setOwner -> reuseNamespace looks up the prefix on the new
	owner, finds nothing, and throws DOMException NAMESPACE_ERR.

Repro options:
	1. Unit-level (fastest, no zkcml needed):
	     cd zktest
	     ./gradlew test \
	         --tests "org.zkoss.zktest.zats.test2.B104_ZK_5686Test"
	   Before the fix the test fails at clone with NAMESPACE_ERR;
	   after the fix it passes.

	2. Linter-level (mirrors the original report):
	     ./gradlew publishToMavenLocal       # in zk/
	     cd ../zkcml/zklinter
	     ./gradlew runLinter
	   Before the fix you see "Failed to include Zul file" / namespace
	   errors on B104-ZK-5686.zul (because the linter clones the
	   included tree). After the fix the linter parses cleanly.

Note:
	Loading this page in a browser does not by itself reproduce the
	bug. The runtime ZUL parser (zk Parser, not idom cloneNode) does
	not take the failing code path, so the page renders with or
	without the fix. Use option 1 or 2 above to verify.
	</label>
	<div viewModel="@id('vm') @init('org.zkoss.zktest.test2.B104_ZK_5686VM')">
		<apply templateURI="B104-ZK-5686-included.zul"/>
	</div>
</zk>
